wikipedia_page.main: Robert Bennett (born 16 June 1940, Bacup) is a former English cricketer who was active from 1958 to 1968. He made his first-class debut in 1962 and appeared in 49 matches as a right-handed batsman who scored 1,814 runs with a highest score of 112.
